[4] USA (Los Angeles County, California)
Date: Tue 6 Aug 2019 11:59 PM PDT
Source: CBSLA Local [abridged, edited]
https://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2019/08/06/measles-union-station/


A person infected with the measles virus traveled through the heavily populated Union Station in Los Angeles.

A person infected with the measles virus traveled through the heavily populated Union Station in Los Angeles, health officials announced [Tue 6 Aug 2019; see source URL above for locations and times of possible exposures.]

There have been 16 measles cases among Los Angeles County residents in 2019, in addition to 9 non-resident measles cases that traveled through Los Angeles County.

