[9] Philippines (Pangasinan, Ilocos)
Date: Thu 8 Aug 2019 6:48 PM PHT
Source: Manila Bulletin [edited]
https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/08/08/9-deaths-from-measles-recorded-in-pangasinan/


Among the 201 laboratory-confirmed measles cases recorded by the Provincial Health Office (PHO) in the province [Pangasinan, Ilocos region] this year [2019], 9 deaths have been attributed to measles.

Dr Anna Ma Teresa de Guzman, provincial health officer [PHO], said the deaths were from the towns of Bani, Villasis, Bolinao, San Fabian and Bautista, and the cities of Dagupan and San Carlos. The town of Mangaldan recorded 2 casualties.

The total number of suspected cases from January to 5 Aug [2019] is 1323, higher than the 179 cases with one casualty in the same period last year [2018], de Guzman said.

The PHO continued to monitor areas with a high number of measles cases. Dagupan had 176 cases; San Carlos City 113; Calasiao 86; Lingayen 86; Alaminos City 76; Malasiqui 69; Bugallon 62; Binmaley 55; Sta Barbara 47; San Fabian 45; Umingan 45; and Bayambang 45.

To head off a measles outbreak, the Department of Health (DOH) has launched in Dagupan school-based immunization program. Around 200 kindergarten and Grade 1 pupils were vaccinated against measles,
diphtheria.

[Byline: Liezle Basa-Inigo]

